A grand concert hall interior in Studio Ghibli style, warm golden lighting illuminating velvet seats and ornate balconies. In the center aisle, multiple doorways materialize like shimmering portals, each showing the same beautiful stage with musicians performing - but viewers are confused, being directed by ethereal spirits toward different entrances based on arbitrary criteria. Floating ribbons of soft light connect all the portals, suggesting they should merge into one unified entrance. The architecture blends art nouveau curves with whimsical fantasy elements, featuring sweeping organic lines and dreamlike atmospheric perspective. Soft watercolor textures, gentle shadows, and a palette of amber, deep burgundy, and midnight blue create an enchanting yet slightly absurd scene highlighting the inefficiency of separated pathways leading to the same destination.
